    "created_at": "2016-10-11T23:26:56Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-10-12T05:27:44Z",
    "body": "Not sure if this was fixed but it works for me now (electron `1.4.2`) with dev-tools open on Windows. Note, it is important to set the width and height, otherwise it would not work. Also, this only works when dragging from within the regular top area.\n\n``` js\n...\nwin = new BrowserWindow({\n  frame: false\n});\n...\n```\n\n``` html\n...\n<head>\n  <style media=\"screen\">\n    html, body {\n      -webkit-app-region: drag;\n      width: 100%;\n      height: 100%;\n    }\n  </style>\n</head>\n...\n```\n"
  },
